<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="96" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="7.[373,1873,2353,2744]" pageId="7" pageNumber="96">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rambur" authorityYear="1842" box="[439,839,2356,2396]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Lestes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="7" pageNumber="96" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="forficula">
<emphasis box="[439,680,2356,2396]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="96">Lestes forficula</emphasis>
Rambur
</taxonomicName>
is known from the surrounding countries French Guiana (
<bibRefCitation author="Selys Longchamps, E. de" box="[387,579,2406,2446]" journalOrPublisher="Bull. Acad. r. Belg." pageId="7" pageNumber="96" pagination="288 - 338" part="13" refId="ref5527" refString="Selys Longchamps, E. de, 1862. Synopsis des agrionines. Seconde legion: Lestes. - Bull. Acad. r. Belg. (2) 13: 288 - 338 (pp. 3 - 54 of reprint)." title="Synopsis des agrionines. Seconde legion: Lestes" type="journal article" year="1862">Selys, 1862</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Machet, P." box="[597,824,2406,2446]" journalOrPublisher="Opusc. zool. flumin." pageId="7" pageNumber="96" pagination="1 - 16" part="40" refId="ref5381" refString="Machet, P., 1989. Contribution a l'etude des odonates de Guyane Francaise. I. Zygoptera. - Opusc. zool. flumin. 40: 1 - 16." title="Contribution a l'etude des odonates de Guyane Francaise. I. Zygoptera" type="journal article" year="1989">Machet, 1989</bibRefCitation>
as 
<emphasis box="[882,1162,2406,2446]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="96">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rambur" authorityYear="1842" box="[882,1145,2406,2446]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Lestes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="7" pageNumber="96" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="forficula">Lestes forficulus</taxonomicName>
),
</emphasis>
Brazil (
<bibRefCitation author="Selys Longchamps, E. de" box="[1300,1491,2406,2446]" journalOrPublisher="Bull. Acad. r. Belg." pageId="7" pageNumber="96" pagination="288 - 338" part="13" refId="ref5527" refString="Selys Longchamps, E. de, 1862. Synopsis des agrionines. Seconde legion: Lestes. - Bull. Acad. r. Belg. (2) 13: 288 - 338 (pp. 3 - 54 of reprint)." title="Synopsis des agrionines. Seconde legion: Lestes" type="journal article" year="1862">Selys, 1862</bibRefCitation>
) and Venezuela (
<bibRefCitation author="Racenis, J." journalOrPublisher="Acta biol. venez." pageId="7" pageNumber="96" pagination="179 - 226" part="2" refId="ref5464" refString="Racenis, J., 1958. Los Odonatos neotropicales en la coleccion de la Facultad de Agrononu'a de la Universidad Central de Venezuela. - Acta biol. venez. 2: 179 - 226." title="Los Odonatos neotropicales en la coleccion de la Facultad de Agrononu'a de la Universidad Central de Venezuela" type="journal article" year="1958">Racenis, 1958</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="De Marmels, J." box="[571,897,2456,2496]" journalOrPublisher="Odonatologica" pageId="7" pageNumber="96" pagination="333 - 345" part="19" refId="ref5286" refString="De Marmels, J., 1990. An updated checklist of the Odonata of Venezuela. - Odonatologica 19: 333 - 345." title="An updated checklist of the Odonata of Venezuela" type="journal article" year="1990">De Marmels, 1990</bibRefCitation>
). 
<materialsCitation collectingDate="1992-07-31" country="Brazil" location="Santo Amoro" pageId="7" pageNumber="96" specimenCount="1" specimenCount-male="1" stateProvince="Bahia">
A male of this species has also been collected by me during a trip through Brazil (State of Bahia, Santo Amoro, 31.vii.1992,1 
<emphasis box="[1642,1672,2508,2544]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="96">♂</emphasis>
)
</materialsCitation>
. It is highly probable that the species occurs in Surinam.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="97" pageId="7" pageNumber="96" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[373,1873,2353,2744]" lastBlockId="8.[369,1875,459,903]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="97" pageId="7" pageNumber="96">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rambur" authorityYear="1842" box="[439,679,2605,2645]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Lestes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="7" pageNumber="96" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="forficula">
<emphasis box="[439,679,2605,2645]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="96">Lestes forficula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is somewhat similar to the newly described species 
<emphasis box="[1620,1872,2605,2645]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="96">
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. Belle" authorityYear="1997" box="[1620,1866,2605,2645]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Lestes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="7" pageNumber="96" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="basidens">Lestes basidens</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
but the former is characterized by having the inner side of the male superior caudal appendages with a median dilatation and in having the pectoral colour pattern only with a pair of metepimeral spots. In this respect the pectoral colour pattern of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rambur" authorityYear="1842" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Lestes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="forficula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">Lestes forficula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles that of 
<taxonomicName authority="Calvert, 1909" authorityName="Calvert" authorityYear="1909" box="[832,1375,512,552]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Lestes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bipupillatus">
<emphasis box="[832,1131,512,552]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">Lestes bipupillatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Calvert, P. P." box="[1144,1375,512,552]" journalOrPublisher="Ann. Carnegie Mus." pageId="8" pageNumber="97" pagination="73 - 280" part="6" refId="ref5238" refString="Calvert, P. P., 1909. Contributions to a knowledge of the Odonata of the neotropical region, exclusive of Mexico and Central America. - Ann. Carnegie Mus. 6 (1): 73 - 280, pls 1 - 9." title="Contributions to a knowledge of the Odonata of the neotropical region, exclusive of Mexico and Central America" type="journal article" year="1909">Calvert, 1909</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, which seems to be its nearest ally. Some specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rambur" authorityYear="1842" box="[868,1107,562,602]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Lestes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="forficula">
<emphasis box="[868,1107,562,602]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">Lestes forficula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have a weakly developed mid-ventral posterior metasternal spot (fig. 3).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[369,1875,459,903]" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">
I add illustrations of some specifically important details of the male and female of 
<emphasis box="[376,628,713,753]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rambur" authorityYear="1842" box="[376,624,713,753]" class="Insecta" family="Lestidae" genus="Lestes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="forficula">Lestes forficula</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
The dimensions of the specimens studied by me are: Male.— Total length ca. 37; abdomen 29-31; hind wing 19-20; costal edge of stigma in fore wing 1.2­ 1.4. Female.— Total length ca. 37; abdomen 29-30; hind wing 21-22; costal edge of stigma in fore wing 1.3-1.5.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
